Ollama Termux is a porting/distribution fork of Ollama for Android ARM64
(Termux). It preserves the upstream Ollama source tree, MIT license, and
version lineage (published as v<upstream>-termux.N), and adds a Termux-first
distribution flow with mobile-oriented runtime tuning (RAM detection per
Android, big-core thread limit, flash attention on CPU-only, context-window
limits per RAM tier, Vulkan loader path for Android, LD_LIBRARY_PATH fix on
Termux runner subprocesses, Termux-only launcher integrations for Codex VL,
Codex, Qwen Code, Claude Code, Hermes Agent). The Termux distribution work
is maintained by Davide A. Guglielmi and distributed under the MIT license
together with the upstream Ollama codebase.

Upstream project: https://github.com/ollama/ollama
